A Rippin Rosie themed birthday party, probably the cutest thing I could imagine, not Frozen, not Moana but Rippin Rosie at Sophia’s birthday.  Rosie met Sophia surfing out at Pleasure Point.  Sophia was 6 years old, going on 7.  She was  learning to surf with her father, a wonderful father daughter time.  Rosie and I paddled over  to say hello, offer some encouragement.  We were greeted with Sophia’s big sunny smile.  Later Rosie and I went into the beach switched to Rosie surfing with her own board.  I was pushing her back out to the surf and we ran into Sophia and her dad again.  We were able to get some super cute photos with Rosie and Sophia.  A few weeks latter I ran into Sophia’s mom and she told me that Sophia had a Rippin Rosie themed birthday party.  I had no She sent me some pictures of the party and I couldn’t stop smiling.  There was the framed picture of Rosie and Sophia together on their surfboards, a stuffed dog on a surfboard and a cake with a surfing dog.  So cute, so cute!!! We love running into Sophia and her family at the beach.  Sophia always cheers for Rosie in the surf and throws Rosie’s retrieving toy for her when they are on the beach. 

It is always amazing how many smiles Rosie and I see when we are out there surfing.  It is so joyful to surf with Rosie and sharing our stoke with other people makes it even more special.  Thank you all sharing our stoke and grateful we can share some smiles.  It is nice that we can have a positive impact on people just by being out there and sharing our adventures on the internet.  Rosie is looking forward to surfing with Sophia for years to come ❤️😀🤙🤙🤙. @stuntpuppy
